      "title": "Improve Blocked status chip visibility and navigation badge on Execute page",
      "description": "Update the Execute phase top bar and navigation to surface blocked tasks more prominently.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n1. Rename the existing \"Blocked\" status chip to \"⚠️ Blocked on Human\" (using the ⚠️ emoji prefix).\n2. The chip must be conditionally rendered — only visible when the count of tasks with status `blocked` (per Section 7.3.3) is greater than zero. When there are zero blocked tasks, the chip is completely hidden (not greyed out or disabled).\n3. When there are >0 blocked tasks, the Execute page's entry in the phase navigation bar/tabs must update its label to \"⚠️ Execute\" (emoji prefix prepended). This badge must be visible regardless of which phase tab the user is currently viewing, so the user is alerted even when on Spec, Plan, Eval, or Deploy.\n4. When blocked count returns to zero (user unblocks all tasks), both the chip and the navigation label revert to their default states (chip hidden, nav label back to \"Execute\").\n5. The blocked count should be derived from the same data source that drives the epic card task statuses (beads issue state), ensuring consistency.",
